      • filterIntegrations

        @GET
 @Produces(value="application/json")
public java.lang.String filterIntegrations(@Context
                                                                                     javax.ws.rs.core.HttpHeaders headers,
                                                                                     @Context
                                                                                     javax.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse response,
                                                                                     @QueryParam(value="filter")
                                                                                     java.lang.String filter,
                                                                                     @QueryParam(value="last")
                                                                                     java.lang.String last,
                                                                                     @QueryParam(value="count")
                                                                                     java.lang.String count,
                                                                                     @QueryParam(value="summary_only")
                                                                                     java.lang.String summary_only)
        Filter Integrations for All Bots There are two filter options: non_fatal and with_build_results. * non_fatal: Integrations with a result of type succeeded, test-failures, build-errors, warnings, analyzer-warnings or build-failed. * with_build_results: Integrations containing build summary information. NOT TESTED
        Parameters:
        headers - HTTP Headers
        response - Http response
        filter - Filter (non_fatal, with_build_results)
        last - The last specified number of integrations
        count - The total number of integrations.
        summary_only - A Boolean value that indicates whether to return a brief summary instead of the regular payload.
        Returns:
        Output from XCode Server
